FIRST_USER_MESSAGE='New approved task: E0.5_backend_module_selection_and_database_split only.  This is a read-only architecture review plus documentation task. Do not implement backend APIs yet. Do not modify Java source unless I explicitly approve after this review. Do not modify Android-apk. Do not modify model-service. Do not modify rehealth-android.  Workspace root: D:\rehealthAI  Target repo: D:\rehealthAI\backend  New requirement: ReHealth backend needs two databases: 1. software database:    - users    - device binding    - user profile    - health interview    - CVD feature vectors    - risk results    - intervention plans    - intervention feedback    - admin/business records  2. hardware database:    - high-concurrency wearable/ring telemetry    - heart rate    - blood oxygen    - blood pressure    - temperature    - sleep    - steps    - HRV    - RRI/PPG metadata if allowed    - raw upload batch logs    - data quality flags  We want to use JeecgBoot microservice modules for: - gateway routing - service discovery/config - rate limiting/circuit breaking - system/user/role/permission management - future service splitting - high-concurrency data ingestion  Before editing anything, inspect: - D:\rehealthAI\backend\README.md - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\pom.xml - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-server-cloud\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-server-cloud\jeecg-cloud-gateway\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-server-cloud\jeecg-cloud-nacos\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-server-cloud\jeecg-system-cloud-start\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-server-cloud\jeecg-demo-cloud-start\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-module-system\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-boot-module\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-boot-base-core\ - D:\rehealthAI\backend\jeecg-boot\jeecg-boot-module\jeecg-module-demo\src\main\java\org\jeecg\modules\rehealth\ if it exists - D:\rehealthAI\model-service\docs\API_CONTRACT.md - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\docs\FEATURE_EXTRACTOR.md  Your tasks:  1. Map local JeecgBoot modules. List all backend modules relevant to: - system/user/role/permission - gateway - nacos/config - cloud start modules - demo module - base core - codegen/online modules if present - job/MQ/sharding/distributed lock support if present  2. Decide what ReHealth needs. Classify modules as: - Required for MVP - Required for high-concurrency / microservice deployment - Useful later - Not needed now / postpone  3. Propose service architecture. At minimum evaluate: - rehealth-mobile-service - rehealth-ingest-service - rehealth-risk-orchestration-service - rehealth-admin-service - model-service as external Python service  4. Propose database architecture. Design: - software_db - hardware_db  For each database, document: - owner service - table categories - read/write pattern - expected concurrency - retention strategy - whether it needs transaction consistency - whether it should be MySQL/PostgreSQL/time-series/ClickHouse/other - MVP implementation choice - production implementation choice  5. Propose data flow. Document: - Android measurement upload flow - hardware data ingestion flow - MQ or async write flow - feature extraction and risk evaluation flow - latest data cache flow - model-service call flow  6. Inspect existing untracked rehealth backend code. Answer: - what files exist; - whether they use @IgnoreAuth; - whether they are mock-only or in-memory; - whether they should be adopted, refactored, or replaced; - whether they fit the new dual-database/microservice design.  7. Update E1 recommendation. Produce a revised E1 implementation plan: - what E1 should implement now; - what should move to E2; - what code should not be written yet; - exact allowed files; - exact endpoint list; - exact docs to update.  Required output files: - D:\rehealthAI\backend\docs\BACKEND_MODULE_SELECTION.md - D:\rehealthAI\backend\docs\DATABASE_SPLIT_ARCHITECTURE.md - D:\rehealthAI\backend\codex-runs\2026-07-09\E0_5_status.md  Validation: - Do not run heavy builds unless needed. - Run git status. - Confirm no Android/model-service/rehealth-android files changed. - Commit documentation changes if possible with:   docs(backend): define module selection and database split  Definition of done: - JeecgBoot module map documented. - Required/postponed modules classified. - Dual database architecture documented. - High-concurrency ingestion path documented. - Existing rehealth package inspected. - Revised E1 plan documented. - E0_5_status.md written. - git status shown. - no source code changes unless explicitly justified.'
